<L>__{exterior shaolin temple day}
<A>__{establishing shot of san de writing bold, black calligraphy on a bare}
<B>__{white paper.}
<A>__{the camera follows the sweeping brush, as it ends with a flourish. the camera pulls back to reveal the temple courtyard, where san de and the d.s. are standing in front of the group of disciples.}
<C>__{san de}
<D>__{only one trial remains before you become full fledged fighting monks. the wooden man chamber.}
<B>__{angle on the disciples}
<A>__{they are remembering the stories they have heard about the chamber.}
<C>__{san de }
<D>__{i warn you all, any monk who fails must leave the temple forever, and will never be called shaolin.}
<A>__{san de pauses, letting this remark sink in.}
<C>__{san de }
<D>__{disciple drew carson, as you will return to america, and never intended to live as a monk in the temple, you need not enter the chamber.}
<B>__{angle on drew}
<A>__{who rises to the challenge.}
<C>__{drew}
<D>__{master san de, i am part of the disciple class, am i not?}
<A>__{san de nods.}
<C>__{drew }
<D>__{then i must pass this final test. furthermore, i request that i be the first one through.}
<C>__{san de}
<P>__{(very proud)}
<D>__{your request is granted.}
<B>__{angle on drew}
<A>__{in front of the entrance to the wooden man chamber. san de and d.s. are flanking drew as he pauses in front of the door. drew turns to look at san de, and the d.s. smacks drew in the back of the head.}
<C>__{drew }
<D>__{what did you do that for?}
<C>__{d.s.}
<D>__{my last chance when you come out the other side, we will be equals.}
<A>__{drew smiles at the d.s.'s attempt to lighten him up. he turns to look at the others from his disciple class, then opens the door and goes through.}
